The paper discusses parallelization strategies for Ant Colony Optimization (ACO) algorithm on Graphics Processing Units (GPUs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, ACO is a meta-heuristic algorithm used for solving optimization problems, which falls under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also discusses programming strategies for the GPU, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. ACO is a population-based algorithm, which involves constructing and updating tours, suggesting that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the ACO algorithm, which could suggest that it belongs to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
